<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900905-0079</DOCNO><DOCID>900905-0079.</DOCID><HL>   REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:   Mass. Exodus</HL><DATE>09/05/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14</SO><CO>   TAXES</CO><IN>ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)</IN><LP>   States such as New York and New Jersey, whose politiciansare currently playing Russian roulette with their economies,might consider what it would be like to have the AP run aheadline like this about them: &quot;Poll Finds Many WouldConsider Leaving Massachusetts.&quot; Just out in Massachusetts,the poll found an incredible 47% saying they'd considergetting out if things got worse. One-third of those polledsay they're cutting back on groceries. Meanwhile, withWashington budget summiteers reconvening soon, an entirenation waits to see if it'll be trapped by a tax increase.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>